#Week 1:
##Lecture 1: Evidence for evolution 
- [What is evolution?](http://ncse.com/evolution) on National Center for Science Education.
- [Why Do So Many Have Trouble Believing In Evolution?](http://www.npr.org/blogs/13.7/2012/01/18/145338804/why-do-so-many-have-trouble-with-evolution) - on NPR.
- [Lampsilis mussel video](https://d19vezwu8eufl6.cloudfront.net/geneticsevolution/source_videos%2FMussel.mp4)
- [Science, religion, and society: The problem of evolution in America](http://onlinelibrary.wiley.com/doi/10.1111/j.1558-5646.2012.01664.x/abstract) by [Jerry A. Coyne](http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Jerry_A._Coyne)
- [NIH Talking glossary of genetics terms](http://www.genome.gov/Glossary/) - on National Human Genome Research Institute.
- [NIH Glosario hablado de términos genéticos](http://www.genome.gov/GlossaryS/) - on National Human Genome Research Institute.

